# SCSS & Styling Conventions

## Token system

All design tokens live in `src/styles/tokens/` and are forwarded through `_index.scss`:

| File | Contents |
|------|----------|
| `_colors.scss` | Backgrounds, text hierarchy, accent, borders, heatmap palette, tooltip |
| `_typography.scss` | Font stacks (display/body/mono), weights, type scale, leading, tracking |
| `_spacing.scss` | Spacing scale, page gutter/max-width, radii, breakpoints |

Import tokens in any SCSS module with `@use '../../styles/tokens' as *;` (adjust path depth).

## Color palette

Earthy, warm tones — not the default GitHub greens:
- Background: `$color-bg` (#f5f2ed), elevated: `$color-bg-elevated` (#ffffff)
- Accent: `$color-accent` (#c8442e) — used for selection highlight and role accents
- Heatmap: `$color-heatmap-empty` through `$color-heatmap-l4` (cream → dark brown)

## Typography

Three font stacks with distinct roles:
- **`$font-display`**: Instrument Serif — profile name, hero headings
- **`$font-body`**: Inter — body text, UI labels, chat messages
- **`$font-mono`**: JetBrains Mono — code-like elements, stats

Type scale goes from `$type-scale-xs` (0.75rem) to `$type-scale-hero` (7rem).

## Breakpoints

Prefix is `$bp-` (bp = breakpoint):
- `$bp-sm`: 640px
- `$bp-md`: 960px
- `$bp-lg`: 1280px
- `$bp-xl`: 1536px

Use `@media (max-width: $bp-md)` for mobile/tablet overrides.

## SCSS Modules

Every component has a colocated `.module.scss` file. Use `composes` sparingly — prefer token variables directly. Class names use camelCase in TypeScript (`styles.repoStack`).

## Global styles

`global.scss` handles:
- Google Fonts import (Instrument Serif, Inter, JetBrains Mono)
- Base font-size (16px, 14px on small screens)
- Selection color using `$color-accent`
- `prefers-reduced-motion` — disables all animations/transitions globally
